return .{ .x = x, .y = y, .width = width, .height = height };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns a new Rect inset by `margin` on all sides.\n    /// Uses saturating subtraction to prevent underflow.\n    /// Position shifts inward; dimensions shrink by 2*margin (or to zero).\n    pub fn inner(self: Rect, margin: u16) Rect {\n        const double_margin = @as(u32, margin) * 2;\n\n        return .{\n            .x = self.x +| margin,\n            .y = self.y +| margin,\n            .width = if (double_margin >= self.width) 0 else self.width - @as(u16, @intCast(double_margin)),\n            .height = if (double_margin >= self.height) 0 else self.height - @as(u16, @intCast(double_margin)),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns area (width * height) as u32 to prevent overflow.\n    pub fn area(self: Rect) u32 {\n        return @as(u32, self.width) * @as(u32, self.height);\n    }\n\n    /// Returns true if rect has zero area.\n    pub fn isEmpty(self: Rect) bool {\n        return self.width == 0 or self.height == 0;\n    }\n\n    /// Clamp a point to be within this rect (inclusive of boundaries).\n    /// Returns the closest point inside the rect.\n    pub fn clamp(self: Rect, x: u16, y: u16) Position {\n        const max_x = self.x +| (self.width -| 1);\n        const max_y = self.y +| (self.height -| 1);\n\n        return .{\n            .x = std.math.clamp(x, self.x, max_x),\n            .y = std.math.clamp(y, self.y, max_y),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns the right edge x coordinate (exclusive).\n    pub fn right(self: Rect) u16 {\n        return self.x +| self.width;\n    }\n\n    /// Returns the bottom edge y coordinate (exclusive).\n    pub fn bottom(self: Rect) u16 {\n        return self.y +| self.height;\n    }\n\n    /// Returns true if the given point is within    }\n};\n\n/// Modifier key state (ctrl, alt, shift).\npub const Modifiers = packed struct {\n    ctrl: bool = false,\n    alt: bool = false,\n    shift: bool = false,\n    _padding: u5 = 0,\n\n /// Tab key.\n    tab: void,\n\n    /// Shift+Tab (backtab).\n    backtab: void,\n\n    /// Backspace key.\n    backspace: void,\n\n    /// Escape key.\n    escape: void,\n\n    /// Arrow keys.\n    up: void,\n    down: void,\n    left: void,\n    right: void,\n\n    /// Navigation keys.\n    home: void,\n    end: void,\n    page_up: void,\n    page_down: void,\n\n    /// Edit keys.\n    insert: void,\n    delete: void,\n\n    /// Function keys (1-12).\n    f: u8,\n\n    /// Create a char KeyCode from a Unicode codepoint.\n    pub fn fromChar(c: u21) KeyCode {\n        return .{ .char = c };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a function key KeyCode (F1-F12).\n    /// Returns null if n is not in range 1-12.\n    pub fn fromF(n: u8) ?KeyCode {\n        if (n >= 1 and n <= 12) {\n            return .{ .f = n };\n        }\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is a printable character.\n    pub fn isChar(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return self == .char;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is an arrow key.\n    pub fn isArrow(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .up, .down, .left, .right => true,\n            else => false,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is a navigation key (arrows, home, end, page up/down).\n    pub fn isNavigation(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .up, .down, .left, .right, .home, .end, .page_up, .page_down => true,\n            else => false,\n        };\n    }\n};\n\n/// Modifier key state (ctrl, alt, shift).\npub const Modifiers = packed struct {\n    ctrl: bool = false,\n    alt: bool = false,\n    shift: bool = false,\n    _padding: u5 = 0,\n\n    /// No modifiers pressed.\n    pub const none: Modifiers = .{};\n\n    /// Create modifiers with only ctrl.\n    pub fn ctrl_only() Modifiers {\n        return .{ .ctrl = true };\n    }\n\n    /// Create modifiers with only alt.\n    pub fn alt_only() Modifiers {\n        return .{ .alt = true };\n    }\n\n    /// Create modifiers with only shift.\n    pub fn shift_only() Modifiers {\n        return .{ .shift = true };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if any modifier is pressed.\n    pub fn any(self: Modifiers) bool {\n        return self.ctrl or self.alt or self.shift;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if no modifiers are pressed.\n    pub fn none_pressed(self: Modifiers) bool {\n        return !self.any();\n    }\n};\n\n/// scroll_down,\n\n    /// Check if this is a click event (down or up).\n    pub fn isClick(self: MouseKind) bool {\n        return self == .down or self == .up;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is a };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a function key KeyCode (F1-F12).\n    /// Returns null if n is not in range 1-12.\n    pub fn fromF(n: u8) ?KeyCode {\n        if (n >= 1 and n <= 12) {\n            return   resize: Size,\n\n    /// Timer tick event (for animations, polling).\n    tick: void,\n};\n\n/// Keyboard event with key code and modifier state.\npub const Key = struct {\n    code: KeyCode,\n    modifiers: Modifiers = .{},\n};\n\n/// Key codes for keyboard input.\n/// Covers standard terminal key sequences.\npub const KeyCode = union(enum) {\n    /// Unicode codepoint for printable backspace: void,\n\n    /// Escape key.\n    escape: void,\n\n    /// Arrow keys.\n    up: void,\n    down: void,\n    left: void,\n    right: void,\n\n    /// Navigation keys.\n    home: void,\n    end: void,\n    page_up: void,\n    page_down: void,\n\n    /// Edit keys.\n    insert: void,\n    delete: void,\n\n    /// Function keys (1-12).\n    f: u8,\n\n    /// Create a char KeyCode from a Unicode codepoint.\n    pub fn fromChar(c: u21) KeyCode {\n        return .{ .char = c };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a function key KeyCode (F1-F12).\n    /// Returns null if n is not in range 1-12.\n    pub fn fromF(n: u8) ?KeyCode {\n        if (n >= 1 and n <= 12) {\n            return .{ .f = n };\n        }\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is a printable character.\n    pub fn isChar(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return self == .char;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is an arrow key.\n    pub fn isArrow(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .up, .down, .left, .right => true,\n            else => false,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is a navigation key (arrows, home, end, page up/down).\n    pub fn isNavigation(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .up, .down, .left, .right, .home, .end, .page_up, .page_down => true,\n            else => false,\n        };\n    }\n};\n\n/// Modifier key state (ctrl, alt, shift).\npub const Modifiers = packed struct {\n    ctrl: bool = false,\n    alt: bool = false,\n    shift: bool = false,\n    _padding: u5 = 0,\n\n    /// No modifiers pressed.\n    pub const none: Modifiers = .{};\n\n    /// Create modifiers with only ctrl.\n    pub fn ctrl_only() Modifiers {\n        return .{ .ctrl = true };\n    }\n\n    /// Create modifiers with only alt.\n    pub fn alt_only() Modifiers {\n        return .{ .alt = true };\n    }\n\n    /// Create modifiers with only shift.\n    pub fn shift_only() Modifiers {\n        return .{ .shift = true };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if any modifier is pressed.\n    pub fn any(self: Modifiers) bool {\n        return self.ctrl or self.alt or self.shift;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if no modifiers are pressed.\n    pub fn none_pressed(self: Modifiers) bool {\n        return !self.any();\n    }\n};\n\n/// Mouse event with position, kind, and modifiers.\npub const Mouse = struct {\n    x: u16,\n event kind.\npub const MouseKind = enum {\n    down,\n    up,\n    drag,\n    move,\n    scroll_up,\n    scroll_down,\n\n    /// Check if this is a click event (down or up).\n    pub fn isClick(self:  home: void,\n    end: void,\n    page_up: void,\n    page_down: void,\n\n    /// Edit keys.\n    insert: void,\n    delete: void,\n\n    /// Function keys (1-12).\n    f: u8,\n\n    /// Create a char KeyCode from a Unicode codepoint.\n    pub fn fromChar(c: u21) KeyCode {\n        return .{ .char = c };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a function key KeyCode (F1-F12).\n    /// Returns null if n is not in range 1-12.\n    pub fn fromF(n: u8) ?KeyCode {\n        if (n >= 1 and n <= 12) {\n            return .{ .f = n };\n        }\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is a printable character.\n    pub fn isChar(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return self == .char;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is an arrow key.\n    pub fn isArrow(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .up, .down, .left, .right => true,\n            else => false,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is a navigation key (arrows, home, end, page up/down).\n    pub fn }\n};\n\n/// Modifier key state (ctrl, alt, shift).\npub const Modifiers = packed struct {\n    ctrl: bool = false,\n    alt: bool = false,\n    shift: bool = false,\n    _padding: u5 = 0,\n\n    /// .{ .shift = true };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if any modifier is pressed.\n    pub fn any(self: Modifiers) bool {\n        return self.ctrl or self.alt or self.shift;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if no
